Sentencas: Polarization properties of catalyzed anode, which we developed for medium-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cells, were examined in a synthetic gas containing H-2, CO2, and H2O.
Titulo: High-performance electrode for medium-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cells - Polarization property of ceria-based anode with highly dispersed ruthenium catalysts in (H-2+CO2+H2O) gas

Sentencas: The overpotential was greatly decreased by loading only a small amount of Ru microcrystals onto the mixed conducting oxide, samaria-doped ceria (SDC), anode layer in both synthetic gas and wet hydrogen atmospheres.
Titulo: High-performance electrode for medium-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cells - Polarization property of ceria-based anode with highly dispersed ruthenium catalysts in (H-2+CO2+H2O) gas

Sentencas: It was found that the Ru-SDC anode exhibited the highest electrocatalytic activities at an optimum oxygen partial pressure in the fuel gas due to high conductivities of both electrons and oxide ions in the SDC.
Titulo: High-performance electrode for medium-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cells - Polarization property of ceria-based anode with highly dispersed ruthenium catalysts in (H-2+CO2+H2O) gas

Sentencas: The maximum current density on the Ru-SDC anode exceeded 1 A/cm(2) at all the operating temperatures between 800 and 1000 degrees C at the potential of -0.9 V vs. air reference electrode, when 0.1 mg/cm(2) of Ru micro-catalysts were loaded on the SDC surface and the appropriate fuel gas was used.
Titulo: High-performance electrode for medium-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cells - Polarization property of ceria-based anode with highly dispersed ruthenium catalysts in (H-2+CO2+H2O) gas
